reviews.text:
*Had no Cap VC so subbed Inw Custard @2.25%*&#xD;
I try everything I mix right after a shake and  almost trashed this one, it's awful fresh.&#xD;
After three weeks it's AMAZING, It's rich but not too much, sweet but not too much. This is easily one of the best recipes i've ever tried.&#xD;
Thank you so much!&#xD;

I think I'm in love. Amazing recipe, good job man!&#xD;
&#xD;
Some details for those still not sure about the recipe. The primary flavor above all in the recipe is Classic for Pipe Dark, which is just an absolutely lovely pipe tobacco flavor that is very spicy and earthy compared to the other for Pipe series from Inawera. I think some people enjoy Black for Pipe over this one, which is a very similar flavor, but personally I like Dark better than Black for Pipe. Most of the other flavors in the recipe help with sweetness and creaminess. If you've never tried a tobacco recipe like this before, this might not sound too appealing, but it is most definitely a very delicious result IMO. If you're looking for a different kind of taste and are only missing a flavor or two this is definitely worth a shot. &#xD;
&#xD;
Also, if you don't have Liquid Amber I feel this ingredient is not 100% essential in my humble opinion, but it'll certainly help.
